data.body:
@arturitu Good catch! I removed the 2nd branch of the if statement below that it is redundant and ends up doubling the height in 3DOF headsets with no `stageParameters` that seems to be the case in Daydream. I do not have a Daydream to test on and did not catch that combination. Google donations to the cause are accepted 😸  

````javascript
if ( pose.position !== null ) {
     
     poseObject.position.fromArray( pose.position );

} else {

    poseObject.position.set( 0, scope.userHeight, 0 );

}
````

@danrossi Thanks for giving it a try. Can you try this branch and let me know if it works for you? https://github.com/dmarcos/three.js/tree/r89fixGood
It has an older version of the PR without the following patch:
````
--- a/src/renderers/webvr/WebVRManager.js
+++ b/src/renderers/webvr/WebVRManager.js
@@ -112,7 +112,7 @@ function WebVRManager( renderer ) {

                        poseObject.position.fromArray( pose.position );

-               }
+               }

                if ( pose.orientation !== null ) {

@@ -120,10 +120,8 @@ function WebVRManager( renderer ) {

                }

-               poseObject.updateMatrixWorld();
-
                var stageParameters = device.stageParameters;
-
+
                if (stageParameters) {
                  standingMatrix.fromArray( stageParameters.sittingToStandingTransform );
                } else {
@@ -131,7 +129,8 @@ function WebVRManager( renderer ) {
                }

                standingMatrixInverse.getInverse( standingMatrix );
-               poseObject.matrixWorld.multiply( standingMatrix );
+               poseObject.position.applyMatrix4( standingMatrix );
+               poseObject.updateMatrixWorld();
                camera.matrixWorldInverse.multiply( standingMatrixInverse );

                if ( device.isPresenting === false ) return camera;
````
